working  at  an  AT&T  call  center  in  southwestern  Virginia,  an  area  suffering  from 
the  decline  of  the  coal  and  tobacco  industries.  They’ll  tell  you  that  building  a  fiber 
backbone  to  their  region  was  literally  a  lifeline  for  themselves  and  their  families. 
Or  ask  Daniel  and  Karen  Fortin  of  rural  northern  Vermont,  who  told  us  that  their 
